Former New York Governor Mario Cuomo has passed away. President Obama and his wife, Michelle, expressed their sadness at the news and praised Cuomo's life of public service. Born to immigrant parents in Queens, Cuomo combined his faith in God and faith in America to become a champion of progressive values. He believed in tolerance, inclusiveness, fairness, dignity, and opportunity for all Americans. The President and First Lady extended their condolences to Cuomo's family and the people of New York who loved him dearly.